{
  "text": "In this section, we consider Rayleigh flat fading channels for computer simulations. The results are averaged over 1000 channel realizations with \u03b3 A = \u22125(dB), \u03b3 B = \u22125(dB), \u03b3 E = \u221215( dB). We also assume that 60% of the SI at node A and node B has been eliminated through digital cancellation [CITATION_1] .",
  "citation_candidates": [
